The late Speaker of Oyo State House of Assembly, Michael Adeyemo, will be buried on Thursday. He will be laid to rest at his hometown in Lanlate, Ibarapa North East Local Council Development Area of Oyo State. The decision was taken at Sunday night’s meeting by the burial planning committee and approved by Governor Abiola Ajimobi. Thursday’s funeral service will be preceded by a valedictory plenary and lying in state at the House of Assembly, Agodi Secretariat, Ibadan. Adeyemo died last Friday of suspected heart attack at Jericho Specialist Hospital in Ibadan. He was 47. 